    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix nfapi_vnf_start_req not returning error codes properly\n\n### Summary\nThe function `nfapi_vnf_start_req()` was not properly returning error codes when messages failed to send. This was caused by the underlying `vnf_send_p5_msg()` function always returning 0, even when SCTP send operations failed. This fix ensures proper error propagation.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/vnf/src/vnf.c`: \n  - Modified `vnf_send_p5_msg()` to return -1 on SCTP send failures\n  - Fixed trace message levels in `nfapi_vnf_pnf_list_find()`\n  - Corrected return value in NR version when AERIAL not enabled\n\n### Reproduction\nWhen calling `nfapi_vnf_start_req()` with an invalid P5 index or when the underlying SCTP connection is broken, the function would previously return success (0) even though the start request message was never actually sent. With this fix, it properly returns -1 to indicate the failure.\n\nUsers may have observed that their VNF start requests appeared to succeed but the PNF never received the start command, leading to stalled initialization sequences.\n"
}